      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>[charisma success]"Still easy to tell, eh? 'Once a Guard always a Guard,' my father used to say. I thought he meant something else, like some higher calling or something. Turns out he meant that once the habits are drilled into you, they stay with you until you die.

"As for how I joined the other side, well, such things happen more often than you think. When a village kid signs up, he wants to be a hero. He wants to stroll into his village in shiny armor and bed every girl. Instead, he gets to do twenty-five hard years and watch his friends die over nothing. When he realizes what he's gotten himself into, he's in the wasteland. A long way from home."</npc_text>
