    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Esbenus</portrait>
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>"They say that raiders fuck up once. One mistake and you're dead.

"The group that took me in made a mistake falling for a 'fake retreat' trick. I saw it coming and tried to warn them, but in the heat of the battle, nobody listened to me. I didn't stick around and left while I still could.

"My next group fared better, until a desert storm forced us to seek shelter. We saw a mountain up ahead and pressed on, despite being blinded by the storm. When we had reached the mountain, we could see that it wasn't what we had expected. There was a temple carved into its façade with a small entrance to what appeared to be a cave. It was a strange place and now, I doubt it was a cave at all. My men tried to warn me – no, the irony isn't lost on me, but I dismissed their warnings as tribal superstitions and paid dearly for it. Only a handful of us got out alive.

"And so I went from one group to another, until I had had enough of the wasteland and decided to move south in search of greener pastures."</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
        <dlgAnsw>
          <text>"What happened in that cave?"</text>
