    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Esbenus</portrait>
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>"It reeked of death. Skulls and bones everywhere... My men begged me to leave, told me that they'd heard stories about this place. Bad stories. Still, the storm outside was real, the stories ... well, stories. People tell them for different reasons – to amuse, to scare, or to keep other people away.

"It got me thinking. The "cave" was small. The walls were rough, but seemingly man-made. You didn't have to be smart to know that there was more to it than that one small chamber. I told my men that these walls must hold great treasure – that was enough for them to abandon their caution and start looking."</npc_text>
