    <dlgPart>
      <portrait>Esbenus</portrait>
      <speaker_name />
      <npc_text>"After hours of searching, we had stumbled upon a switch. It opened a hidden passage leading to another two chambers. The first one contained two strange objects – each one as tall as a man. They were indistinguishable – carbon copies of each other, just sitting there untouched. You could mistake them for some idols, if not for the metal pipes that disappeared into the floor. There were no clues as to their purpose or the reason why someone needed two of them.

"The second chamber had metal pipes running along the walls and was empty, save for a single platform. It was like a metal cart with railings. I remember wondering who would possibly waste so much metal to build such a contraption. Then, Nicanor stepped onto it and the platform went down – all the way through the floor and into the very depths of the underworld, judging by the noise and red glow.

"Soon, the platform returned. Without him."</npc_text>
      <onLoadScripts />
      <answers>
